quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  41,26,"The disbelievers say: \"Do not listen to this Qur’an and make noise when it is recited so that you may gain the upper hand"
  41,27,We will certainly punish the disbelievers and requite them for the worst of their misdeeds
  41,28,"hell that is, the reward for such enemies of Allah, which will be their eternal home: a reward for their denying Our revelations"
  41,29,"Wherein, the disbelievers will say: \"Our Lord! Show us those among jinns and mankind who misled us: we shall trample them under our feet so that they become utterly disgraced"
  41,30,"As for those who say: \"Our God is Allah,\" and then stay firm on it, the angels will descend on them, saying: \"Let nothing fear or grieve you. Rejoice for the good news of paradise that has been promised to you"
  41,31,We are your protectors in this life and in the hereafter. There you shall find all that your souls desire and all that you can ask for
  41,32,"A hospitable gift from the All-Forgiving, All-Merciful"